      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "That&#39;s the most accurate answer. Should be the accepted one. E.g. a method which takes a <code>java.lang.Object</code> will also accept a reference of any interface type. Moreover you can cast interface to an <code>Object</code> implicitly without any compiler error."
